  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor/Senior Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist in preparation of tender submission;</li>\n  <li>Responsible for measurement of quantities &amp; cost estimation;</li>\n  <li>Call quotations, compare prices and prepare bill of quantities to arrive the tender pricing;</li>\n  <li>Study contract documents, perform measurements and prepare Bill of Quantities;</li>\n  <li>Assist in contract administration, prepare progress claim(s) and liaise with the Client’s representative on claims and variation costs;</li>\n  <li>Prepare budget statement monthly and review by Superior;</li>\n  <li>Review and verify the Subcontractor’s / Supplier’s claims and prepare payment certificates and to obtain approval from relevant parties</li>\n  <li>To maintain the Quality System in the Department;</li>\n  <li>Be responsible for any other duties that may be assigned from time to time as your superior / Management deem fit.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirement</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Degree in Quantity Surveying or equivalent;</li>\n  <li>Minimum <strong>5-8 years’</strong> working experience in tendering, estimating and measurement of quantities on projects;</li>\n  <li>MRT/LTA tendering experience is preferred;</li>\n  <li>Strong analytical and critical thinking skills;</li>\n  <li>Good negotiation, communication and stakeholder management skills;</li>\n  <li>Resourceful, independent and able to work in a fast-paced environment;</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
